 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "R-X3TWtgE5xZ"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Low resolution medical image classification using Feed- forward Neural Networks\n",
    "\n",
    "The database are 64x64 grayscale medical images belonging to 6 classes:\n",
    "*   Abdomen (Computed Tomography)\n",
    "*   Breast (Magnetic Resonance)\n",
    "*   Chest (X-ray)\n",
    "*   Chest (Computed Tomography)\n",
    "*   Hand (Xray)\n",
    "*   Head (Computed Tomography)\n",
    "\n",
    "![inbox_793761_80e9bd2c92dbd64518c8f7be18d57b81_Untitled.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "2P0P4ZBzGiN5"
   },
   "source": [
    "We are going to create a FeedForward artificial neural network capable of classifying these images correctly in their respective categories automatically"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "4h4NDMHYEvLt"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Importing libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "_cell_guid": "b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19",
    "_uuid": "8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5",
    "id": "FGovPkuGIHHf"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "from tensorflow import keras\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, classification_report \n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "_7aG3U3TKAKS"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Reading and pre-procesing the dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 351
    },
    "id": "HzK3bEMvAYWD",
    "outputId": "998ea3cf-c807-49f7-e52e-7258e79433a8"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train = np.load(\"X_train.npy\")/255\n",
    "X_test = np.load(\"X_test.npy\")/255\n",
    "y_train = np.load(\"y_train.npy\")\n",
    "y_test = np.load(\"y_test.npy\")\n",
    "print (X_train.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "93XvXPPOWt-d"
   },
   "source": [
    "# We draw the class distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "W_PbYbtUV4i1"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class_name_list = ['ABDOMENCT', 'BREASTMRI', 'CHESTXR', 'CHESTCT', 'HANDXR', 'HEADCT']\n",
    "class_len_list = np.bincount(np.argmax(y_train, axis=1))\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Label distribution')\n",
    "ax.bar(class_name_list,class_len_list, color = ['r', 'g', 'b', 'y', 'c', 'm'])\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "r5GN7Cp8KtlE"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Creating a Keras ImageDataGenerator for training and test subsets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "iIZDOBTsK-xu"
   },
   "source": [
    "This allows us to have a reliable image generator from the dataset that we can use to train and test the model. This generator just outputs images from the original dataset in random order to the model until it stops training.\n",
    "\n",
    "It is also very useful to apply transformations in real time to the images. In this case, we apply the rescale=1./255 to change each pixel value from 0-255 to 0-1. This helps Neural Networks to avoid the Exploding Gradients problem."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "7U89QjfwIHH5"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "train_datagen = image.ImageDataGenerator()\n",
    "train_datagen.fit(X_train)\n",
    "train_generator = train_datagen.flow(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "test_datagen = image.ImageDataGenerator()\n",
    "test_datagen.fit(X_test)\n",
    "test_generator = test_datagen.flow(X_test, y_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "jCYu6ZxyN4dS"
   },
   "source": [
    "# **Creating and training the model**\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "VQMmud6UNRaR"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Defining Model Architecture"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "qordnLI1IHH8"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([\n",
    "        tf.keras.Input(shape=(64, 64, 3)),\n",
    "        tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),\n",
    "        tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n",
    "        tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),\n",
    "        tf.keras.layers.Dense(6, activation='softmax')])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "vADMB3txNlxN"
   },
   "source": [
    "We compile the model using:\n",
    "*    loss: categorical_crossentropy\n",
    "*    optimizer: adam"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "xHrlHqfgIHH8"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "opt = keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.00001)\n",
    "model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=opt, metrics=['acc'])\n",
    "model.summary()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "PP5vhcQUN8yB"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Fitting the model using the ImageDataGenerator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "8yfnwG3YGIzT"
   },
   "source": [
    "We create an early stopping callback that stops the training process when the validation accuracy does not improve for 10 epochs. It also restores the best weights when training process is done."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "8H_jLJPEIHH9"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fit_history = model.fit(\n",
    "        train_generator,\n",
    "        validation_data=test_generator,\n",
    "        steps_per_epoch=len(train_generator),\n",
    "        epochs=200,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "s8epnlY1OHC7"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Validating Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "G73q0xk6GAEJ"
   },
   "source": [
    "We plot the train/test loss and accuracy evolution during training process"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "gHpfuGvwIHH-"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "loss_train = fit_history.history['loss']\n",
    "acc_train = fit_history.history['acc']\n",
    "epochs = len(loss_train)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20, 6))\n",
    "for i, metrics in enumerate(zip([loss_train, acc_train], ['Loss', 'Accuracy'])):\n",
    "    plt.subplot(1, 2, i + 1)\n",
    "    plt.plot(range(epochs), metrics[0], label='Training {}'.format(metrics[1]))\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "AmcseuTXCEzJ"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "loss_test = fit_history.history['val_loss']\n",
    "acc_test = fit_history.history['val_acc']\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(20, 6))\n",
    "for i, metrics in enumerate(zip([loss_test, acc_test], ['Loss', 'Accuracy'])):\n",
    "    plt.subplot(1, 2, i + 1)\n",
    "    plt.plot(range(epochs), metrics[0], label='Test {}'.format(metrics[1]))\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Ou5nexgWUnFt"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Final evaluation along Testing set "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "cee7hNfRUvsv"
   },
   "source": [
    "Accuracy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "NkqqlYbBIHH_"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "result  = model.evaluate(test_generator,steps=len(test_generator))\n",
    "print('Loss:', result[0])\n",
    "print('Accuracy:', result[1])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "LC_feW7jIHzL"
   },
   "source": [
    "Predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "YDQQhqNaIHIB"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nn_pred = model.predict(X_test)  \n",
    "y_pred = np.argmax(nn_pred, axis=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "bQo2k5wH5qpp"
   },
   "source": [
    "Confusion matrix"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "ik61Rln7IHIC"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nn_cm = confusion_matrix(np.argmax(y_test, axis=1), y_pred, normalize='true')\n",
    "nn_df_cm = pd.DataFrame(nn_cm, ['ABDOMENCT', 'BREASTMRI', 'CHESTXR', 'CHESTCT', 'HANDXR', 'HEADCT'], ['ABDOMENCT', 'BREASTMRI', 'CHESTXR', 'CHESTCT', 'HANDXR', 'HEADCT'])  \n",
    "plt.figure(figsize = (10,5))  \n",
    "sns.set(font_scale=1.4) #for label size  \n",
    "sns.heatmap(nn_df_cm, annot=True, annot_kws={\"size\": 12}) # font size  \n",
    "plt.show() "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "miPzy_rRITBZ"
   },
   "source": [
    "And see how each class performs using different metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "DcjiL3ivIHID"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nn_report = classification_report(np.argmax(y_test, axis=1), y_pred)  \n",
    "print(nn_report)"
   ]
  }
 ],
